}{}$G_i$\end{document}, called interaction blocks in this work, by using the density-based algorithm DBSCAN (14). This algorithm utilizes the fact that the clustered points tend to have high local density and the isolated points tend to have low local density. In the calculation, the point density is defined to be the number of points located in the spatial sphere at a given radius. Two parameters, i.e. the minimum number of points and the spatial radius, are involved in this calculation. Previous work (20) has discussed how to set these two parameters, and our calculation follows this procedure.

